	<Title>
		Using a fitness ball? Pick the right size
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Fitness balls come in various sizes. For most exercises, you&apos;ll want a ball that allows your knees to be at a right angle when you sit on the ball with your feet on the floor. The firmer the ball, the more difficult the exercise will be. So if you&apos;re just starting out, you might want to slightly deflate the ball. You can add more air as you gain strength and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
